Description:
This is the sniffer application that collects visible mac-addresses and
sends them to the backend for data processing.

How to use:
1. Install golang and tshark/wireshark (apt-get, pacman, etc)
2. $ source setup-env.sh
   (Let's fetch the dependencies)
3. $ go get github.com/golang/glog          Logging tool
4. $ go get github.com/ogier/pflag          POSIX style flags
6. Edit the code (optional)
7. $ cd src/github.com/digit-chalmers/hubbit-sniffer/
8. $ go install
9. Start monitor mode on the wireless interface. (Requires aircrack-ng to be installed)
   # airmon-ng start wlan0
10. Set dumpcap to run as root (to allow monitoring without sudo) sudo chmod 4755 /usr/bin/dumpcap
11. $ hubbit-sniffer --help
12. $ screen -S hubbit-sniffer -U hubbit-sniffer

